>
  <p>
    When one person says their septic repair was minor and another says theirs was major, they're
    usually talking about different parts of the same kind of system. A septic setup is a chain: the
    tank and its baffles, sometimes a pump, the pipes connecting everything, a distribution box, and
    the drain field. Each link can fail in its own way, and knowing the chain is what makes a
    provider's diagnosis and recommendation understandable rather than mysterious.
  </p>

  {/* Intended asset: /images/resources/common-septic-system-repairs-hero.webp — see public/images/resources/README.md */}
